h3cwapiMIB.name: h3cwapiMIB
h3cwapiMIB.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cwapiMIB.description: H3C-WAPI-MIB is an extension of MIB in WAPI protocol. This MIB contains objects to manage configuration and monitor running state for WAPI feature.

h3cwapiModeEnabled.name: h3cwapiModeEnabled
h3cwapiModeEnabled.description: When this object is set to TRUE, it shall indicate that WAPI is enabled. Otherwise, it shall indicate that WAPI is disabled.

h3cwapiASIPAddressType.name: h3cwapiASIPAddressType
h3cwapiASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set global IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of AS.

h3cwapiASIPAddress.name: h3cwapiASIPAddress
h3cwapiASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the global IP address of AS.

h3cwapiCertificateInstalled.name: h3cwapiCertificateInstalled
h3cwapiCertificateInstalled.description: This object indicates whether the entity has installed certificate. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the entity has installed certificate. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the entity hasn't installed certificate.

h3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.name: h3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors
h3cwapiStatsWAISignatureErrors.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI signature is wrong.

h3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors
h3cwapiStatsWAIHMACErrors.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI message authentication key checking error occurs.

h3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures
h3cwapiStatsWAIAuthRsltFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI authentication result is unsuccessful.

h3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters
h3cwapiStatsWAIDiscardCounters.description: This counter increases when the received packet of WAI are discarded.

h3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.name: h3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters
h3cwapiStatsWAITimeoutCounters.description: This counter increases when the packet of WAI overtime are detected.

h3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors
h3cwapiStatsWAIFormatErrors.description: This counter increases when the WAI packet of WAI format error is detected.

h3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures.name: h3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures
h3cwapiStatsWAICtfHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI certificate authenticates unsuccessfully.

h3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures
h3cwapiStatsWAIUniHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI unicast cipher key negotiates unsuccessfully.

h3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures.name: h3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures
h3cwapiStatsWAIMulHskFailures.description: This counter increases when the WAI multicast cipher key announces unsuccessfully.

h3cwapiConfigTable.name: h3cwapiConfigTable
h3cwapiConfigTable.description: The table containing WAPI configuration objects.

h3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType.name: h3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType
h3cwapiConfigASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set IP addresses type of AS.

h3cwapiConfigASIPAddress.name: h3cwapiConfigASIPAddress
h3cwapiConfigASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the IP address of AS.

h3cwapiConfigAuthMethod.name: h3cwapiConfigAuthMethod
h3cwapiConfigAuthMethod.description: This object selects a mechanism for WAPI authentication method. The default is certificate.

h3cwapiConfigAuthMode.name: h3cwapiConfigAuthMode
h3cwapiConfigAuthMode.description: This object selects a mechanism for WAPI authentication mode. When the value is standard, it shall indicate that the entity acts accord with the official definition. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the entity finishs authentication by means of RADIUS. The default is standard.

h3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled.name: h3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled
h3cwapiConfigBKRekeyEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the BK rekey function is supported. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the BK rekey function is supported. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the BK rekey function is not supported.

h3cwapiConfigExtTable.name: h3cwapiConfigExtTable
h3cwapiConfigExtTable.description: The table containing WAPI configuration objects for SSID.

h3cwapiConfigExtEntry.name: h3cwapiConfigExtEntry
h3cwapiConfigExtEntry.description: An extend entry in the h3cwapiConfigExtTable.

h3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID.name: h3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID
h3cwapiConfigServicePolicyID.description: Represents the ID of each service policy.

h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled.name: h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled
h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherEnabled.description: This object enables or disables the unicast cipher.

h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.name: h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize
h3cwapiConfigUnicastCipherSize.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the unicast cipher key. This should be 256 for SMS4, first 128 bits for encrypting, last 128 bits for integrity checking.

h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled.name: h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled
h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled.description: This variable indicates the corresponding AKM suite is enabled or disabled.

h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite.name: h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite
h3cwapiConfigAuthenticationSuite.description: The selector of an AKM suite. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType.name: h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType
h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddressType.description: This object is used to set IP addresses type of AS.

h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress.name: h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress
h3cwapiCfgExtASIPAddress.description: This object is used to set the IP address of AS.

h3cwapiCfgExtASName.name: h3cwapiCfgExtASName
h3cwapiCfgExtASName.description: This object is used to set the name of AS.

h3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain.name: h3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain
h3cwapiCfgExtCertDomain.description: This object is used to set the PKI domain name.

h3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled.name: h3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled
h3cwapiCfgExtCertInstalled.description: This object indicates whether the entity has installed certificate. When the value is TURE, it shall indicate that the SSID has installed certificate. Otherwise, it shall indicate that the SSID hasn't installed certificate.

h3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate.name: h3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate
h3cwapiUserwithInvalidCertificate.description: This trap is sent when a user intrudes upon network with invalid certificate.

h3cwapiStationReplayAttack.name: h3cwapiStationReplayAttack
h3cwapiStationReplayAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker records and replays network transactions.

h3cwapiTamperAttack.name: h3cwapiTamperAttack
h3cwapiTamperAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker monitors network traffic and maliciously changes data in transit(for example, an attacker may modify the contents of a WAI message).

h3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack.name: h3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack
h3cwapiLowSafeLevelAttack.description: This trap is sent when a station associates AP(Access Point), creates packet of Unicast Key Negotiation Response with wrong WIE(WAPI Information Element) of ASUE(Authentication Supplicant Entity).

h3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack.name: h3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack
h3cwapiAddressRedirectionAttack.description: This trap is sent when an attacker maliciously changes destination MAC address of WPI(WLAN Privacy Infrastructure) frame.

h3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr.name: h3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr
h3cwapiTrapInfoMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the WAPI user.

h3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId.name: h3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId
h3cwapiTrapInfoBSSId.description: As MAC Address format, it is to identify BSS.
